Package com.inrupt.client.core

Class InputStreamBodySubscribers<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrupt.client.core.InputStreamBodySubscribers<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type into which the InputStream is mapped.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpResponse.BodySubscriber<T>, Flow.Subscriber<List<ByteBuffer>>
    public final class InputStreamBodySubscribers<T>
extends Object
implements HttpResponse.BodySubscriber<T>
    This class provides a convenience method for mapping an HTTP response from an InputStream to a custom type.

    For example, writing a custom HttpResponse.BodySubscriber to parse a JSON response payload into a custom type can be performed in the following way: 

    
     public static HttpResponse.BodySubscriber<VerifiablePresentation> ofVerifiablePresentation() {
         return InputStreamBodySubscribers.mapping(input -> {
             try (var stream = input) {
                 return processor.fromJson(stream, VerifiablePresentation.class);
             } catch (IOException ex) {
                 throw new UncheckedIOException("Error parsing presentation", ex);
             }
         });
     }

    After consuming an InputStream, please be sure to close the resource.
